      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "BELLINGHAM, March g.\nCounty officers here are having\ntrouble with negro laborers import\ned by ]. J. Hill to replace Japs on\nthe Great Northern. The negroes\nhave been quarantined but refuse\nto remain in the camps. They are\narmed and threaten any officer who\nattempts to enforce restrictions.\nRace trouble is feared."
